dc:description: Year 24 of Severus Antoninus. For the account of Phaophi [=Sept/Oct 215 AC] Tourbon made a partial payment of four drachmas, =4 drachmas, to Aurelius Ptollas the collector of the monodesmia of hay, and for Mesore [=July/Aug 216 AC] sixteen drachmas, =16 drachmas.
